Package util

Class Duration

java.lang.Object
util.Duration
public class Duration extends Object
Represents a duration of time between a start and end point.

  • Constructor Details

    • Duration

      public Duration(UTCTime start, UTCTime end)
      Constructs a new Duration object from a start and end time.
      Parameters:
      start - the start time of the duration.
      end - the end time of the duration.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if start == null.
      IllegalArgumentException - if end == null.

    • Duration

      public Duration(int hours, int minutes, int seconds, int millis)
      Constructs a new Duration object from quantities of each unit of time.
      Parameters:
      hours - the number of hours in the duration, on the interval [0, inf).
      minutes - the number of minutes in the duration, on the interval [0, 60).
      seconds - the number of seconds in the duration, on the interval [0, 60).
      millis - the number of milliseconds in the duration, on the interval [0, 1000).
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if hours < 0.
      IllegalArgumentException - if minutes < 0 || minutes >= 60.
      IllegalArgumentException - if seconds < 0 || seconds >= 60.
      IllegalArgumentException - if millis < 0 || millis >= 10000.
